A 45-year-old man, Hassan Mohammed, was on Friday arraigned before an Ojo Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, for allegedly being in possession of stolen goods. The defendant is standing trial on two counts of conspiracy and receiving stolen goods, offences he denied committing. The prosecutor, Insp. Simon Uche told the court that the defendant committed the offences on April 7, 2017, in Ojo. ALSO READ: Kogi Chief of Staff launches youth empowerment foundation He said that the goods belonging to the complainant, one Bashiru Yusuf, known as PK products, were found in custody of the defendant. Two arraigned for allegedly robbing woman with knife Appointment of caretaker committees in Oyo: The court and… Man docked for stealing car accessories worth N67,000 Court denies Orji Kalu bail pending appeal According to the prosecution, the defendant conspired with some others, who are now at large, to receive the PK products knowing the same to be stolen goods. The goods were valued at N6.5 million. The offences contravene the provisions of Sections 328 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, Mr A.A.Adesanya granted the defendant bail in the sum of N1 million with two sureties in like sum. He adjourned the case until Feb. 4 for mention. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
